**BOOM!** `__free_page(page)` is called *immediately*!

The asynchronous read is *still in flight* and pointing to that now freed memory! This means the block device will DMA into a **freed page**! **Use-After-Free** of the page! And even worse, the data written to `zram` in `zram_write_page` is going to contain uninitialized kernel memory (besides the partial bytes), and that's an **info leak**! And when that read completes, it will overwrite the freed page, corrupting whatever memory it is currently being used for! And the read completion will call `bio_endio(parent)` on the WRITE bio (which is `parent`)! This will complete the parent bio early, or decrement its remaining count incorrectly!

